Key Match Events: Paul Skenes pitched two scoreless innings in the Pirates' 9-4 win over the Yankees.
Skenes struck out Juan Soto and Aaron Judge in the first inning.
Skenes finished his rookie campaign with a 99.6 mph fastball to retire Jazz Chisholm Jr.
Post-Match Reflections: Paul Skenes expressed his satisfaction with finishing the season strong and doing it against the Yankees' lineup.
Manager Derek Shelton praised Skenes' performance and potential for growth.
Skenes reflected on the season, acknowledging the success of the workload management plan and his readiness for the next season.
